Resolution Description: 1.27-[OPTIMA]-Latest examples have been shared with the suppliers 1.22-[OPTIMA]- We had a meeting with the user and suppliers and below is the inference : User to share the AWBs which they are unable to see in the queue (as directed by RMS team). We will share those with the suppliers to check why these are not being reflected in the pricing queue. Also, we will initiate another email thread to track a separate issue in which users are unable to see the updated booking in systems . We suspect that this might well be due to the fact when both users (optima and ciber) are the same person but we have seen in the past that somebody is doing something in Optima and tries to check how awb looks in Ciber immediately after. We shall then involve RMS and CIBER , if required. 1.21-[OPTIMA]-Meeting has been setup between users and suppliers for tomorrow 1.19-[OPTIMA]-We are checking this internally 1.11--[OPTIMA]- Chaser has been sent to the users 1.7-[OPTIMA]-The suppliers updated that no action was taken by the user with the given AWB as well. The first version of booking was queued and later same was accepted in the second version. On the third version booking amendment was done via CIBER. Again the fourth version of booking is queued. Incident Description: No hemos recibido los ficheros de Xeerpa para el día 29 de Septiembre
BA Reference Number: 1174959
Resolution Description: 1.28-[OPTIMA]- Please find the below response from AFLS: As we discussed earlier the reason revenue was null for some versions is that there are no corresponding records in booking info and booking rated tables and as explained earlier, it’s an existing behavior. In the last discussion, MIS user requested to check for all other scenarios where Optima is performing partial commits in DB and upon checking we could see that for some of the bookings, the records were available in booking table and were not available in customer table. On further analysis, we could see that there is booking confirmation message coming from CIBER/BA80 with customer information, this is the reason records were not available in customer table for the respective booking and this is another scenario where partial commit is happening. Currently pending with the user to advise 1.27-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.25-[OPTIMA]-Currently pending with the suppliers 1.22-[OPTIMA]-Update from AFLS: As mentioned in previous email, we could see the records found in booking & booking_leg tables and not available in customer table. On further analysis could see there are confirm booking we are receiving without customer details from CIBER & BA80 and there no customer details for booking with other airline prefix. Since this is not like a partial comment in DB, its valid scenario, so the only scenario we are facing is loose configuration change. Please find the below sample message from CIBER without customer details. "QK XXXXXXX .YYYYYYY 092000 SSN/1 20JAN2021/1020+060 MWB/N/075-42949082/STN-MAD RTG/MADBCN CMD/CONSOL CACESA ITN/IB1130/20JAN/MADBCN/SS//K6T1MC0.067 SPH/A/IBC USR/001AARS/QLM PRI/999999 " Have asked MIS team to check and advise 1.20-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.15-[OPTIMA]- Update from AFLS : We are working on the list of scenario where Optima create records in booking and booking_leg tables and not creating in other booking related tables. As discussed earlier scenario 1 when do modification in loose configuration screen its partial creating records in some of booking tables. On our future testing we could see records found in booking & booking_leg tables and not available in customer table, we are analyzing the scenario on which this pattern of records. Once after the analyze will let you know whether its valid scenario or not, keep post updates on 20th Jan. 1.8-[OPTIMA]-AFLS to provide an update by 15th Jan 1.7-[OPTIMA] - Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.5-[OPTIMA]-AFLS have checked with their BA and internal team for the below and they need to have a code walkthrough to identity all the scenarios, which they need to discuss with architect team and have scheduled call internal tomorrow, once after the call they will share us the ETA. 1.4-[OPTIMA]-We had a meeting and below are the MOMs: Below are the Minutes for the meetings: 1. AFLS mentioned that certain tables (info and rate) are not updated with subsequent versions if loose config is changed. It was also understood that loose config data is not in booking/booking leg hist tables but still they are incremented with versions. IAG IT team has asked AFLS to kindly provide the rationale for change in only subset of tables (and none of them have loose config data). AFLS will discuss this internally and come with answers. 2. IAG IT Team has also asked AFLS on all possible scenarios where related tables are not be updated. With this MIS support and business will have understanding on impact on different fields. 3. AFLS to provide timelines on when they can provide answers to above questions. 12.21-[OPTIMA]-A call will be scheduled on 4th Jan between users/AFLS 12.17-[OPTIMA]-AFLS to provide an update by tomorrow EOD 12.15-[OPTIMA]-AFLS are discussing internally for the next release plan and will let us know the update by Friday EOD. 12.14-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the suppliers 12,10-[OPTIMA]:Chaser sent to suppliers 12.8-[OPTIMA]:Cha

[NDC-SUPPORT] Reserva cancelada por RI con billete emitido (cambio horario no contemplado)
Resolution Description: [TKT]: Análisis El motivo de que no se actualizara el PNR con el SSR TKNE se debe a que cuando se emitió el billete el 31 de Enero a las 13:38h , la emisión se hizo correctamente pero la actualización del PNR con el número de billete falló. Adjuntamos logs del sistema de esa fecha/hora: Time stamp of record 2020-01-31 1338:13 IN Runid: *12D3M Trx code: SYS500 PID: 125 Date: 20-01-31 Time: 1238:13 QE CT/MAD959 **ERROR EN CREACION DE SSR TKNE** 31JAN20 13:38 SCHEDULE CHANGE IN PROGRESS MKCN1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 OVDMAD 475 M12JUL 0752100619650C1 /P1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 MADLHR 3164 M12JUL 0752100619650C2 /P1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 LHRMAD 3171 O01AUG 0752100619650C3 /P1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 MADOVD 482 O01AUG 0752100619650C4 /P1 Cómo se ve, en el momento que se crea el elemento SSR TKNE con el número de billete, se produce un error motivado por un 'SCHEDULE CHANGE IN PROGRESS ' Esto hace que la reserva se quede sin billete y RI la cancele. Estos errores se quedan en la cola CT de MAD959, pero desconocemos que equipo toma acción sobre ellos. No, obstante, vemos, que el estado actual de los billetes es REFUNDED por lo que no es necesaria ninguna acción sobre ellos.

live animal bookings on IB irregualrity
Resolution Description: 2.23-[OPTIMA]-As agreed with the user, we shall monitor this issue till Friday i.e. 26th Feb and shall close it thereafter 2.22-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the users 2.17-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the users 2.15-[OPTIMA]-We had a meeting with WNS guys and AFLS and it was observed that the bookings were referred to two queues, but user accepted the booking from only one queue. Optima will send unsolicited message when the booking gets accepted from all the referred queues. As agreed by the user , it was not processed from LON_RMS_BYPASS queue which was one of the queue. This information has been cascaded to the WNS team for future reference. We would now monitor this case for a couple of days and then close it if we don’t receive any such case again. Please let us know in case of any concern. 2.11-[OPTIMA]-AFLS has requested to have a screen sharing session with the user who is accepting this booking and CIBER team. We will schedule one for monday 2.4-[OPTIMA]-Information has been shared with the suppliers 2.1-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.27-[OPTIMA]-Latest examples have been shared with the suppliers 1.22-[OPTIMA]- We had a meeting with the user and suppliers and below is the inference : User to share the AWBs which they are unable to see in the queue (as directed by RMS team). We will share those with the suppliers to check why these are not being reflected in the pricing queue. Also, we will initiate another email thread to track a separate issue in which users are unable to see the updated booking in systems . We suspect that this might well be due to the fact when both users (optima and ciber) are the same person but we have seen in the past that somebody is doing something in Optima and tries to check how awb looks in Ciber immediately after. We shall then involve RMS and CIBER , if required. 1.21-[OPTIMA]-Meeting has been setup between users and suppliers for tomorrow 1.19-[OPTIMA]-We are checking this internally 1.11--[OPTIMA]- Chaser has been sent to the users 1.7-[OPTIMA]-The suppliers updated that no action was taken by the user with the given AWB as well. We have asked the user to check and let us know accordingly 1.6-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.4-[OPTIMA]-new example has been shared with the suppliers 01.04-[OPTIMA]-Have asked the user to share new samples. 12.24-[OPTIMA]-Clarification has been provided to the user 12.17-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 12.14-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the user 12.10-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the user 12.8-[OPTIMA]-AFLS provided an update as below : We have checked the user reported waybill and see that the 4 versions of booking is available in OPTIMA. The first version of booking was queued and later same was accepted in the second version. On the third version booking amendment was done via CIBER. Again the fourth version of booking is queued. Please refer the below details for your reference. [OPTIMA]Booking dimensions availability
Resolution Description: 4.29-[OPTIMA]-User update : The user cannot create any restrictions. It only requests an availability for certain criteria: - Routing - Date - Commodity - Pieces - Weight - Dimensions - Allocation - etc. Based on the availability response received from Optima, the booking request is made. Therefore, if there is any restriction in Optima for the dimensions of the request, it should not offer availability to the user or at least inform of such restriction. 4.28-[OPTIMA]-Final Chaser has been sent to the user 4.26-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.20-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.19-[OPTIMA]-AFLS updated the following : We have checked the user reported issue and understand that when performing the availability search for MIL - ORD and the length given in the request is 330. And when performing the booking for MXP - ORD the length given in the request is 362.But the user expectation is to reject the booking due to no large booking options for ORD. In OPTIMA we can restrict the bookings based on the length ,width ,height ,MAX_NBR_PIECES ,MAX_WT_PER_PIECE , MAX_SUM_W_L_H by using the PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction. When we were checking for the restriction for the ORD by matching the above attributes we couldn't see PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction created for ORD. Can you please ask the user to create a PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction for ORD to restrict the large bookings ? 4.16-[OPTIMA]-The local office informed the customer that there were no large booking options for ORD, however, those options were shown to the user as available, so the customer asks us if the availability is wrong. Currently pending with AFLS 4.15-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.13-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.9-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.7-[OPTIMA]-Below update from AFLS has been shard with the user : ____________________________________ From the above ticket, we understand that this booking made with the dimensions L x W x H 362x90x299 and booking has been accepted, but the expectation is to reject due to the size of the cargo. Please let us know if our understanding is correct or please explain in detail the issue which you are facing. Could you please check and advise us accordingly ? 4.6-INC20589740 raised at AFLS's end

Incident Description: [OPTIMA]OPTIMA IB- OPTIMA BKG INFLATING BOOKINGS ON IB FLIGHTS (MAKING FLIGHTS LOOK INC0178533
Resolution Description: 4.28-[OPTIMA]-Chaser sent to Jason 4.26-[OPTIMA]-pending with Jason to recreate the scenario 4.20-[OPTIMA]-Information shared with user and AFLS 4.16-[OPTIMA]-Updates from CIBER have been shared with the suppliers 4.15-[OPTIMA]-AFLS have checked the reported flight IB 6621/17-Apr-21 and could see the 075 booking cancellations with this flight via BFE. As mentioned by Simon, this is a known issue and he has advised users to avoid using cancel AWB in BFE. AFLS already had a live session with Jason to perform this scenario in E2E1. Jason has performed the below steps : ?Created a booking via BFE with 125 prefix and IB flight. ?Once the booking confirmed checked the details in OPTIMA and CIBER end and the details has been updated as expected. Then cancelled the booking via BFE and the inventory has been reduced at both OPTIMA and CIBER end. For 075 prefix he faced an issue in creating a booking. AFLS is currently waiting for Jason to test IB booking in E2E1. @Jason Cook : Please advise if we need to have another working session with AFLS . 4.13-[OPTIMA]- INC20434337 has been raised in AFLS's SNOW. new examples have been reported 4.9-Pending with AFLS 4.6-[OPTIMA]-User is unable to test a booking on UAT. We have asked the user to please retry and let us know if you can run a test now ? If still unable, we will ask AFLS to check and advise. 3.30-[OPTIMA]-Simon advised that this is happening due to the IB users trying to use CANCEL AWB which is causing this issue to have mismatch between Optima and CIBER on the booked values and we were advised to check with Jason to check the same in UAT environment. Jason performed a 075 booking on IB flight and tried to CANCEL AWB from IE browser to see the impact. Although it seems to have worked for 125 booking on IB flight from Jason even though AFLS had received error in response from CIBER as below: <OrigMsgInd>X</OrigMsgInd> <MessageSeqNo>1</MessageSeqNo> <RequestStn>HDQ</RequestStn> <UserId>U693908</UserId> <DutyCode>RE</DutyCode> </MessageHead> <Response> <RespInd>E</RespInd> <RespComments>UNABLE TO PROCESS</RespComments> </Response> <AWB_ID> <Prefix>125</Prefix> <Number>30033006</Number> Could you please keep us informed if many users are still seeing this issue? We have been informed that Simon has advised users to avoid using cancel AWB in BFE. [OPTIMA]:[OPTIMA]:INC20434337 raised with suppliers Assigned SNOW ticket ref. no. INC0178533
